                    {
                        "name": "Ectoplasmic Form",
                        "type": "offensive_action",
                        "text": "An elder wyrmwraith can push through the ectoplasmic veil to temporarily assume a physical form made of ectoplasm. The elder wyrmwraith loses the incorporeal trait for 1d4 rounds, though it can return to its incorporeal form as a free action before then. Once this ability ends, the elder wyrmwraith can\u2019t use this ability again for 1d4 rounds. While in ectoplasmic form, the elder wyrmwraith\u2019s AC increases to 52 and it gains 125 temporary Hit Points. It loses its immunity to non-magical attacks and precision damage, as well as its resistance to all damage. Its claw and jaws Strikes deal slashing and piercing damage, respectively, instead of negative damage.",
                        "action": {
